column5: That looks like a great day. Beauty fish, nice sunny day, and calm seas.
Very nice!!
Beauty brownies! Nicely done  Look at the gut on the brown in the 2nd pic!

Couldn't take it with with the weather so nice we had to splash the boat.  And when we got to the ramp at 6:30 we realized we weren't the only ones.  We had to get away from the pack  ( and the ass in the white Lund that wanted to troll up my bum and over my lines)       I have never tried spring Browns bufore but they are a funny fish they try and swim past the boat when you hook them. crazy buggers , makes it entertaining in the small boat .   This little football      And big fish of the day    Great to be out and catch a few fish. But it only gets better from here !
Nice!!!  Great shooting guys?  Browns sure are a purdy fish!
nice
nice going. cant wait till  I can finally get out.
Awesome stuff man
Nice football browns!
Nice!
Cool, I'm jealous
The guy in the batman hat, is his name Dan H.?
nicely done. Keep telling myself I will try that some spring but it never happens....maybe next year
Very nice guys
MY GAWD, there are greasers everywhere.  Nice fish dudes.

Beauty day you had there Freshtrax. We are talking about splashing the boat and heading to Big "O" for some close to shore Browns. I'll wait a week or 3 because if I get the boat in the water I guarantee March goes out like a Lion.
Great fish gents. Love those Browns.
Nicely done !!!!!
Very nice Andrew!
he is a river rat from the Barrie area named mark.   Thanks for the kind words guys, fun to put some sun on my face and a bend in a rod that's for sure.
Nice. Where did you launch from?
Heading home from work this morning I saw a Lund on the Redhill Parkway heading towards lake O..
that could have been me.  would have been heading north on the red hill parkway, towing my lund, around 9am'ish.
Some nice football shape brownies!
Nice!
no need to be on the lake at 7am for browns, lol.  :)
Nice man!  What kind of water temps were you seeing out there?
